## ğŸ”‘ Quick Reference (Most Important Terms)

Think of this section as your **flashcards**. If you only remember these, youâ€™ll have the big picture.  

- **Artificial Intelligence (AI)** â€“ Teaching machines to mimic human thinking and decision-making.  
- **Machine Learning (ML)** â€“ Teaching machines to **learn from data** instead of just following rules.  
- **Deep Learning (DL)** â€“ A type of ML that uses **neural networks with many layers** (like a digital brain).  
- **Generative AI (GenAI)** â€“ AI that can **create new things** (text, images, music, etc.).  
- **Transformers** â€“ A model architecture that lets AI **understand context and relationships in data** (the engine behind GPT).  
- **Large Language Models (LLMs)** â€“ Very large transformer models trained on text.  
- **Prompt Engineering** â€“ Writing good instructions for AI to get better results.  
- **Zero-Shot / Few-Shot Learning** â€“ AI can do tasks with **no examples (zero)** or **just a few examples (few)**.  
- **Fine-Tuning** â€“ Adjusting a pre-trained AI model for a **specific task or industry**.  
- **Chain-of-Thought Prompting** â€“ Asking AI to **show its reasoning step by step**.  
- **RLHF (Reinforcement Learning with Human Feedback)** â€“ Teaching AI by combining machine learning with **human corrections**.  
- **Responsible AI** â€“ Making sure AI is **fair, safe, and ethical**.  

